jobs_results.description:
Fing is the #1 network scanner for mobile with more than 50 million downloads across its mobile and desktop apps. Our patented technology is used by top Internet providers and device manufacturers worldwide.

Fing is consolidating into a single platform to help people with their networks across multiple apps, website and appliances.

Working together with the product team, this is a great opportunity to work across the full project lifecycle, involved with all levels of the business that reaches millions of people every month.

At Fing we are building a new way to consider the home network as an integral part of the domestic experience, including network security, consumer-grade troubleshooting and home protection.

Now we are looking for passionate engineers that are self-driven, experienced and eager to continuously learn new technologies. If you are interested in joining an incredibly fun and talented mobile team and get a chance to work with not just software but with hardware as well, we look forward to hearing from you!
What you'll do
• Join an autonomous development team dedicated to creating a seamless user experience across mobile and web applications
• Collaborate with peers in product design, QA, cloud operations and embedded teams
• Evaluate new frameworks and tools to help guide the future of the Fing app
• Support the growth of the engineering team through thoughtful leadership and mentorship
• Act as a thought leader when it comes to evaluating new frameworks and tools for the app

We're looking for someone who...
• Has three or more years of iOS development experience, must have knowledge of Objective-C, Swift and Swift UI;
• Can show their code of published apps currently available in the App Store;
• Has experience with app performance optimization, multithreading, low-level networking;
• Knows Human Interface Design Guidelines and is aware of other platform’s guidelines;
• Can have high-level architectural discussions about how to grow the Fing app (familiar with MVP, Clean or MVVM and can evaluate the benefits of each);
• Has a BS/MS degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related subject;
• Lives in Rome on nearby;
• Understands how to balance immediate product needs with long-term project health and maintainability;
• Is comfortable working with a fast-paced release schedule;
• Has problem-solving abilities, attention to detail, and effective communication skills;
• Is passionate about staying up to date with the latest trends and advancements in mobile app development;

Bonus Points

Side projects, contributions to open-source projects

Has developed custom and reusable components

Familiar also with Android paradigms

Has worked to build consumer experiences

Our offer you can't refuse

Working with leading tools and newest technology

Fulltime long-term contract with a competitive wage

Extra company benefits like Ticket Restaurants, extra Health Insurance, Pension Plan

Flexible working hours

Teleworking budget

Internal and external training

Central and convenient office location
